[baby crying]

00:17.016 --> 00:20.019
<i>[Donna Summer's "I Feel Love"]</i>

00:20.103 --> 00:22.313
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:22.397 --> 00:27.360
[babies screaming]

00:27.444 --> 00:30.363
[baby crying]

00:30.447 --> 00:37.537
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:46.087 --> 00:52.093
<i>- ♪ I feel love ♪</i>

00:52.177 --> 00:54.053
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:54.137 --> 00:56.806
<i>♪ I feel love ♪</i>

00:56.890 --> 00:58.767
[baby crying]

00:58.850 --> 01:01.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:01.561 --> 01:08.276
<i>♪ I feel love ♪</i>

01:08.359 --> 01:09.319
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:09.402 --> 01:15.909
<i>♪ I feel love ♪</i>

01:15.992 --> 01:23.082
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:30.215 --> 01:33.551
<i>[serious music]</i>

01:33.635 --> 01:38.556
[indistinct chatter,
car doors closing]

01:38.640 --> 01:43.895
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:43.978 --> 01:45.438
- I got it. I got it.

01:45.522 --> 01:48.024
It doesn't bend well,
that's all.

01:48.107 --> 01:50.151
The right knee
is the worst one.

01:50.235 --> 01:51.653
There you go.

01:51.736 --> 01:54.197
- You skinny guys
will have to sit at the end.

01:54.280 --> 01:57.367
[laughter]

01:58.368 --> 02:01.830
- Dick, you've been doing this

02:01.913 --> 02:03.540
probably longer than any of us.

02:03.623 --> 02:06.376
I mean, you must have
some stories about--

02:06.459 --> 02:08.044
- Oh, sure.

02:08.127 --> 02:10.338
[hoarsely] This little boy
was waiting...

02:10.421 --> 02:12.215
[clears throat]
In line.

02:12.298 --> 02:16.094
And he was just jumping,
and he held his hands,

02:16.177 --> 02:19.389
and he was smiling
like crazy, you know?

02:19.472 --> 02:23.893
And, like, he just could
not wait to get to see Santa.

02:23.977 --> 02:26.855
And so, finally, it's his turn.

02:26.938 --> 02:28.898
And I says,
"And so how are you?"

02:28.982 --> 02:31.734
And he says,
"I pooped!"

02:31.818 --> 02:34.696
[laughter]

02:34.779 --> 02:36.155
- So I've got one.

02:36.239 --> 02:38.199
A lot of times they'll say,

02:38.283 --> 02:41.578
"All right, if you're the real
Santa, what's my name?"

02:41.661 --> 02:43.246
- Oh, I got that one.

02:43.329 --> 02:46.291
- And usually what I say is,
"Listen, I only know

02:46.374 --> 02:50.920
"the names of the children
on the nice list.

02:51.004 --> 02:53.298
I don't know your name."

02:53.381 --> 02:56.009
[laughter]

02:56.092 --> 02:58.052
- So I got a call
to book a Santa.

02:58.136 --> 03:00.722
And she said, "Is he white?"

03:00.805 --> 03:05.560
And I was like,
"Well, yeah, I mean...

03:05.643 --> 03:09.272
all the Santas
I have are white."

03:09.355 --> 03:13.568
So I'm thinking about trying
to bring on people

03:13.651 --> 03:14.819
who can--

03:14.903 --> 03:16.529
so you can offer Santas

03:16.613 --> 03:19.824
who aren't kind of
the cookie cutter,

03:19.908 --> 03:23.828
white, 65 years old, fat.

03:25.872 --> 03:28.124
Now, some clients
will disagree

03:28.207 --> 03:31.210
because they have
a very specific thing

03:31.294 --> 03:33.046
they want in their Santa.

03:33.129 --> 03:34.339
- The way I explained it
one time

03:34.422 --> 03:36.299
when I got challenged
on it was,

03:36.382 --> 03:39.427
well, I started with
the history of Santa, okay?

03:39.510 --> 03:41.846
Santa originated

03:41.930 --> 03:44.641
in the European continent,

03:44.724 --> 03:49.062
and the predominant
population was white.

03:49.145 --> 03:50.313
So Santa would be white.

03:50.396 --> 03:51.689
- Actually--
- That's wrong.

03:51.773 --> 03:55.818
Jesus Christ and St. Nicholas

03:55.902 --> 03:58.988
would have been brown,
not white.

03:59.072 --> 04:00.657
- I'm talking about trying
to explain

04:00.740 --> 04:01.908
to a four-year-old child

04:01.991 --> 04:04.494
why she can't have
a Black Santa.

04:04.577 --> 04:07.413
- It doesn't matter.

04:07.497 --> 04:11.292
It just doesn't matter
whether they're gay,

04:11.376 --> 04:15.838
they're white,
they're Jewish, they're Black.

04:15.922 --> 04:18.508
Being the oldest member
of this group,

04:18.591 --> 04:21.344
for my generation, at first,

04:21.427 --> 04:24.847
this was a little difficult
to accept.

04:24.931 --> 04:28.851
But God created no junk.

04:28.935 --> 04:30.061
You know?

04:30.144 --> 04:32.188
So it doesn't matter.

04:33.398 --> 04:36.567
<i>[light music]</i>

04:36.651 --> 04:39.195
[engine turning over]

04:39.278 --> 04:45.827
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:45.910 --> 04:47.662
- Oh, about ten years ago,

04:47.745 --> 04:51.207
we created
the New England Santa Society.

04:51.290 --> 04:54.252
And it's open for Santas
of all types,

04:54.335 --> 04:58.715
Mrs. Clauses, elves,
and other holiday performers.

04:59.924 --> 05:01.884
We have a lot
of really experienced Santas.

05:01.968 --> 05:06.055
I mean, we have Santas who have
been doing it 30, 40, 50 years.

05:06.139 --> 05:08.474
So we created a school,

05:08.558 --> 05:11.436
which is now called Santa Camp.

05:11.519 --> 05:14.313
<i>It's starting to become</i>
<i>more visible</i>

05:14.397 --> 05:17.358
<i>and we're starting to do</i>
<i>much more promotion of it.</i>

05:17.442 --> 05:20.361
<i>So this is one of</i>
<i>the most popular top reasons</i>

05:20.445 --> 05:21.904
<i>to come to Santa Camp.</i>

05:21.988 --> 05:24.907
<i>We have some photos.</i>
<i>We have some videos.</i>

05:24.991 --> 05:28.703
<i>We do have our kazoo band.</i>

05:28.786 --> 05:32.832
[kazoos playing]

05:32.915 --> 05:35.209
One of the things
I think really sets

05:35.293 --> 05:36.753
our Santa school apart

05:36.836 --> 05:40.048
is that we have been trying
to reach out

05:40.131 --> 05:42.884
to more and more types
of Santas

05:42.967 --> 05:44.927
and Santas
from different backgrounds,

05:45.011 --> 05:46.971
just...

05:47.055 --> 05:50.224
people who are different.

05:50.308 --> 05:54.395
But I think sometimes
the issue we run into

05:54.479 --> 05:58.274
is that people just have
a very...

05:58.357 --> 06:01.569
specific idea of what Santa
should look like.

06:01.652 --> 06:06.449
And I think a lot of times,
it's their childhood Santa,

06:06.532 --> 06:09.202
the one they remember as kids.

06:09.285 --> 06:15.249
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:15.333 --> 06:18.753
<i>- Does Santa need</i>
<i>to have a look?</i>

06:18.836 --> 06:20.379
Well, he's certainly
got to look

06:20.463 --> 06:21.756
something like Santa Claus.

06:21.839 --> 06:25.510
- It must be a red suit,
black belt, beard.

06:25.593 --> 06:29.806
And it's much better
if they can pull it, okay?

06:29.889 --> 06:31.390
- You can get,
like, a heat iron,

06:31.474 --> 06:34.560
and you just kind of curl it
and roll it under.

06:34.644 --> 06:36.979
- The belly can be padded.

06:37.063 --> 06:39.899
Mine is real.
I can't hide that.

06:39.982 --> 06:42.360
- I think people definitely
have an expectation

06:42.443 --> 06:43.986
of how Santa should look.

06:44.070 --> 06:46.447
A few years ago, I understand
that they did hire

06:46.531 --> 06:48.741
a Black Santa
at the Mall of America.

06:48.825 --> 06:50.910
And apparently
it didn't go so well,

06:50.993 --> 06:53.496
and there was a lot
of pushback about it,

06:53.579 --> 06:57.458
and not everybody
was thrilled with the idea.

06:57.542 --> 06:59.794
<i>- A Black Santa Claus</i>
<i>at the Mall of America,</i>

06:59.877 --> 07:01.337
the country's largest mall,

07:01.420 --> 07:04.048
is causing a torrent
of hateful, racist comments.

07:04.132 --> 07:08.636
<i>- With some people online</i>
<i>even calling for a boycott.</i>

07:08.719 --> 07:10.930
- There was some talk
on the Internet,

07:11.013 --> 07:13.474
not from other Santas.

07:13.558 --> 07:18.354
<i>- Unfortunately, in America,</i>
<i>we're not quite at the stage</i>

07:18.437 --> 07:22.984
where everybody can be accepted
as Santa Claus.

07:23.067 --> 07:26.279
<i>- I just don't know</i>
<i>why it's necessary.</i>

07:26.362 --> 07:29.198
I don't understand
why people feel

07:29.282 --> 07:31.033
they need a Black Santa Claus.

07:31.117 --> 07:33.953
Changing the race
is cultural appropriation.

07:35.413 --> 07:38.082
<i>- For all you kids watching</i>
<i>at home, Santa just is white.</i>

07:38.166 --> 07:39.709
<i>How do you just revise it,</i>

07:39.792 --> 07:43.379
you know, in the middle
of the legacy of the story

07:43.462 --> 07:45.214
and change Santa
from white to Black?

07:45.298 --> 07:47.466
<i>I mean, you can't.</i>

07:49.010 --> 07:52.096
[dog barking]

07:55.016 --> 07:58.978
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:59.061 --> 08:02.440
- [lows]

08:02.523 --> 08:04.775
- This is Rudy.
This is our baby.

08:04.859 --> 08:08.571
Look at how big he's grown.
See those antlers?

08:10.323 --> 08:14.202
Santa has reindeer
all over the world,

08:14.285 --> 08:17.705
<i>in case he should have</i>
<i>a problem with the Elite Eight</i>

08:17.788 --> 08:21.083
<i>on his special trips.</i>

08:21.167 --> 08:23.127
You all pooped and tuckered.

08:23.211 --> 08:26.797
Oh, there you go.
You gonna take a little nap?

08:26.881 --> 08:28.257
Santa likes to take a nap

08:28.341 --> 08:31.219
in the afternoon, too,
sometimes, you know?

08:33.679 --> 08:38.100
<i>My role as Mrs. Claus</i>
<i>started in 2006.</i>

08:38.184 --> 08:40.061
<i>I had just retired.</i>

08:40.144 --> 08:43.022
[chuckles] Yeah, I spent 40
years working in engineering,

08:43.105 --> 08:46.692
which was pretty much
a male-dominated field.

08:46.776 --> 08:51.030
So, yeah, so when I make up for
the character as Mrs. Claus...

08:51.113 --> 08:53.908
[scoffs] She ain't being
disrespected, you know?

08:53.991 --> 08:56.994
It's like, I am not
the warm-up act for Santa.

08:57.078 --> 08:59.455
I come in on his arm.
I am his wife.

08:59.538 --> 09:01.958
I am not an elf
doing all those things

09:02.041 --> 09:04.001
that I think the elves do.

09:04.085 --> 09:07.505
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:07.588 --> 09:09.048
Let's see.

09:09.131 --> 09:12.134
Santa loves Mrs. Claus.
Mrs. Claus loves Santa.

09:12.218 --> 09:13.719
There's no doubt about that.

09:13.803 --> 09:17.306
But as the world has changed,
so has Mrs. Claus.

09:17.390 --> 09:19.267
We've come a long way, baby.

09:19.350 --> 09:22.979
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:23.062 --> 09:27.608
In a few weeks, I'm gonna be up
in Manchester, New Hampshire,

09:27.692 --> 09:29.402
at the Santa Camp.

09:29.485 --> 09:31.070
And I'm gonna be doing
a program

09:31.153 --> 09:34.407
with a couple other Santas
and Mrs. Clauses

09:34.490 --> 09:36.617
about issues with Mrs. Claus.

09:36.701 --> 09:38.411
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:38.494 --> 09:41.497
I think everybody wants to be
treated fairly and equally,

09:41.580 --> 09:45.126
and, you know,
that's just the way it is.

09:45.209 --> 09:48.587
But how pushy are you gonna be
about it, you know?

09:48.671 --> 09:52.008
And it's like, "I'm pushy."

09:52.091 --> 09:55.469
[reel whirs, water splashes]

09:55.553 --> 09:59.056
[excited chatter]

09:59.140 --> 10:06.230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:09.608 --> 10:13.446
[people screaming]

10:13.529 --> 10:15.906
- Merry Christmas!
- Hi.

10:15.990 --> 10:18.200
- Yo, Santa!
- Hey, guys. How are you?

10:18.284 --> 10:20.953
- Yeah!
- Good to see you.

10:21.037 --> 10:24.665
- Say cookies!
- Cookies!

10:24.749 --> 10:26.584
- So today there's gonna be
a lot of Santas

10:26.667 --> 10:28.544
running around the park.

10:28.627 --> 10:30.796
<i>Once we're away</i>
<i>from Christmas,</i>

10:30.880 --> 10:34.008
<i>we meet pretty much</i>
<i>every month as a group.</i>

10:34.091 --> 10:35.217
<i>- Hey, Santa.</i>

10:35.301 --> 10:36.844
- Well, hello, there,
young man.

10:36.927 --> 10:39.805
<i>We like to dress up,</i>
<i>have different outfits.</i>

10:39.889 --> 10:41.974
<i>This is our summer</i>
<i>Santa style.</i>

10:42.058 --> 10:45.269
[laughing]

10:45.353 --> 10:47.563
- That shit's going deep!

10:47.646 --> 10:49.190
- Hi!
[baby crying]

10:49.273 --> 10:51.233
Okay.

10:51.317 --> 10:53.944
I thought that
was a smile coming.

10:54.028 --> 10:56.113
[laughs]

10:56.197 --> 10:57.948
Hey, come on over.

10:58.032 --> 11:00.618
Are you gonna get a picture,
or you just want to chat?

11:00.701 --> 11:02.411
- Both!
- All right.

11:02.495 --> 11:04.246
Let's get
a good background here.

11:04.330 --> 11:07.416
We'll get
this banana background.

11:07.500 --> 11:09.335
- A real live Santa Claus.

11:09.418 --> 11:11.295
You have the new kicks.

11:11.379 --> 11:14.006
- No!
These were made by an elf.

11:14.090 --> 11:16.050
[laughter]

11:16.133 --> 11:18.594
- So Santa was, like,
definitely my biggest idol.

11:18.677 --> 11:21.263
That's why I'm, like,
kind of shocked right now.

11:21.347 --> 11:23.474
He was like, my hero,
definitely.

11:23.557 --> 11:25.559
- Have you always seen Santa
as being white?

11:25.643 --> 11:27.937
- Yes. I wish there was, like,
a variety of Santas

11:28.020 --> 11:30.356
that are willing to come
in different colors

11:30.439 --> 11:32.942
to let people know
that they could come

11:33.025 --> 11:35.611
in any different shape
and form, you know?

11:35.694 --> 11:39.073
But that's not how the world,
like, is right now, so...

11:39.156 --> 11:41.784
- But it could change.
- Yeah.

11:41.867 --> 11:44.912
- Yeah, things are changing.
- Hopefully.

11:46.872 --> 11:48.958
You just got to find 'em.

11:49.041 --> 11:49.917
- Yeah.

11:50.000 --> 11:55.798
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:55.881 --> 11:57.675
- Jolly.

11:57.758 --> 12:01.470
<i>Santa Claus is just an idea.</i>

12:01.554 --> 12:05.391
And the fact that a Black child

12:05.474 --> 12:10.146
wants to have a Black Santa,
somebody who looks like them,

12:10.229 --> 12:11.814
what's the problem?

12:11.897 --> 12:14.400
I mean...

12:14.483 --> 12:17.319
that's it.

12:17.403 --> 12:21.198
It's Santa.
[chuckles]

12:21.282 --> 12:24.326
I mean...
[scoffs, sniffles]

12:24.410 --> 12:26.954
[voice breaking]
The look in the kids' eyes

12:27.037 --> 12:29.373
when they meet you, and...

12:29.748 --> 12:31.584
That's what it's about.

12:31.667 --> 12:33.961
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:34.044 --> 12:37.840
[sniffles]
Excuse me.

12:37.923 --> 12:41.135
[blows nose]

12:41.218 --> 12:43.137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:43.220 --> 12:44.638
<i>Here in New Hampshire,</i>

12:44.722 --> 12:48.976
we don't have
huge minority populations,

12:49.059 --> 12:52.688
<i>so we have been reaching out</i>
<i>to people outside New England.</i>

12:53.772 --> 12:55.816
"Black Santa Claus."

12:55.900 --> 12:58.986
<i>And there's a Santa</i>
<i>named Chris.</i>

12:59.069 --> 13:00.446
<i>He's Black.</i>

13:00.529 --> 13:03.115
<i>And he has a heck</i>
<i>of a story to tell.</i>

13:03.199 --> 13:06.619
<i>- A North Little Rock man's</i>
<i>Facebook post is going viral</i>

13:06.702 --> 13:08.996
after showing a letter
he received in the mail.

13:09.079 --> 13:12.166
- He claims that he was
the target of a racist note...

13:12.249 --> 13:15.878
<i>- Attacking him</i>
<i>for not having a white Santa.</i>

13:17.129 --> 13:21.175
- I have never had any problems
out of anybody.

13:22.510 --> 13:26.430
All of a sudden, we got
a problem with Black Santa.

13:28.474 --> 13:30.601
But this man...

13:30.684 --> 13:32.520
he ain't coming down.

13:32.603 --> 13:36.315
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:36.398 --> 13:41.403
<i>We moved to North Little Rock</i>
<i>specifically for our daughter.</i>

13:41.487 --> 13:44.949
We wanted to offer her
a great education

13:45.032 --> 13:47.243
from the very beginning.

13:48.702 --> 13:50.704
- I'm drawing Santa.

13:50.788 --> 13:55.209
No, I'm gonna do
a little bit of brown.

13:55.292 --> 13:57.461
He's kind of chocolaty.

13:58.837 --> 14:00.631
<i>But, you know,</i>
<i>we're Black people</i>

14:00.714 --> 14:05.386
<i>in a predominantly</i>
<i>white neighborhood.</i>

14:05.469 --> 14:09.390
That is the Karen right there.
- Yes.

14:09.473 --> 14:12.560
- She making blocks.
- Yeah, she is.

14:12.643 --> 14:14.645
And she's calling.
- Calling who?

14:14.728 --> 14:18.315
- The police, I guess.
- Psycho.

14:18.399 --> 14:19.775
- When you're walking
by yourself,

14:19.858 --> 14:21.986
that's why I definitely feel
the need

14:22.069 --> 14:24.572
that you need to be
in bright clothing.

14:24.655 --> 14:26.490
Like, I prefer
that your cell phone case

14:26.574 --> 14:30.035
be a bright, obnoxious color
so someone can obviously tell

14:30.119 --> 14:32.705
that it is a cell phone
and not a gun.

14:32.788 --> 14:34.748
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:34.832 --> 14:37.626
- Representation is a big thing
for our family.

14:37.710 --> 14:42.464
<i>And I have a ten-foot-tall</i>
<i>inflatable Black Santa.</i>

14:42.548 --> 14:44.174
<i>One day I checked the mail,</i>

14:44.258 --> 14:47.011
<i>and there was</i>
<i>a letter in there.</i>

14:47.094 --> 14:48.804
<i>I opened it.</i>
<i>I got mad.</i>

14:48.887 --> 14:52.266
<i>I was definitely angry.</i>
<i>In fact, I was livid.</i>

14:52.349 --> 14:55.811
This is the type of people
that I live around.

14:55.894 --> 14:57.187
This is the type of people

14:57.271 --> 14:59.273
that I have to raise
my daughter around.

14:59.356 --> 15:03.736
These are the type of people
that I have to worry about.

15:03.819 --> 15:08.991
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:09.074 --> 15:12.161
This is what I got.

15:12.244 --> 15:15.331
- Can I ask you to read it?
- I really don't want to.

15:15.414 --> 15:17.791
Like, it just...

15:17.875 --> 15:19.585
Yeah.

15:19.668 --> 15:22.254
Because one of the things--
I start stuttering,

15:22.338 --> 15:24.256
and that makes me
even more frustrated.

15:24.340 --> 15:28.927
And so that's why I generally
don't read it out loud.

15:30.095 --> 15:31.430
So, yeah.

15:32.681 --> 15:36.852
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:36.935 --> 15:38.646
- [humming]

15:38.729 --> 15:43.192
<i>- It was 100% an attack</i>
<i>on who I am as a person.</i>

15:43.275 --> 15:47.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:47.404 --> 15:48.864
<i>We, of course, thought,</i>

15:48.947 --> 15:51.992
<i>"Did we pick the right</i>
<i>neighborhood to live in?</i>

15:52.076 --> 15:55.704
<i>And should we be</i>
<i>looking to move?"</i>

15:55.788 --> 15:57.998
That's what we live
next door to.

15:58.082 --> 16:00.376
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:00.459 --> 16:02.628
A stupid Confederate flag.

16:02.711 --> 16:05.506
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:05.589 --> 16:09.301
It's the clear
and present danger for us.

16:09.385 --> 16:11.261
<i>I needed to channel the anger</i>

16:11.345 --> 16:14.556
<i>into something</i>
<i>that wasn't negative.</i>

16:14.640 --> 16:17.226
<i>So I went and rented</i>
<i>a Santa costume</i>

16:17.309 --> 16:21.230
<i>and played Santa Claus</i>
<i>for my daughter.</i>

16:21.313 --> 16:24.775
- Down and across.

16:24.858 --> 16:26.777
<i>- I want to be able to be</i>
<i>Black Santa</i>

16:26.860 --> 16:28.237
<i>for other families.</i>

16:28.320 --> 16:30.823
So I'm gonna be going
up to New Hampshire

16:30.906 --> 16:32.282
to a Santa camp

16:32.366 --> 16:35.744
to learn all the ins and outs
of being Santa.

16:35.828 --> 16:38.664
- This is what I created.

16:38.747 --> 16:43.210
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:46.171 --> 16:47.798
- How long have you been
a Santa?

16:47.881 --> 16:50.467
- I've been a Santa
since I was 16 years old.

16:50.551 --> 16:53.762
I'm 69 years old
in human years now.

16:53.846 --> 16:55.723
So 53 years.

16:55.806 --> 16:58.559
- I have been to Santa Camp
three years in a row.

16:58.642 --> 17:02.563
It helps me connect
with other like-minded people.

17:02.646 --> 17:05.232
- You learn techniques.

17:05.315 --> 17:07.860
And you learn the business

17:07.943 --> 17:11.113
'cause the business
of Santa Claus is very big.

17:11.196 --> 17:13.449
I could easily walk away

17:13.532 --> 17:16.201
with $2,000 a night.

17:16.285 --> 17:18.704
- There's a particular Santa
that comes from Rhode Island.

17:18.787 --> 17:22.040
He's known
as Santa to the Stars.

17:22.124 --> 17:23.917
I mean,
he has a house in Italy.

17:24.001 --> 17:25.794
I mean, he has a house
in California,

17:25.878 --> 17:27.629
and he drives brand-new cars.

17:27.713 --> 17:29.173
- I think there's approximately

17:29.256 --> 17:32.134
5,000 to 6,000
professional Santas.

17:32.217 --> 17:36.180
And you know the whole reason
of having professional Santas

17:36.263 --> 17:38.307
is to improve, like a guild.

17:38.390 --> 17:41.477
- You meet people and learn
from their experiences.

17:41.560 --> 17:43.103
It's like a big family.

17:43.187 --> 17:45.647
- Santa Society is
like a brotherhood.

17:45.731 --> 17:49.318
We quite often call ourselves
"The Brothers in Red."

17:49.401 --> 17:52.529
[distant bell tolling]

17:54.573 --> 17:58.160
<i>[light music]</i>

17:58.243 --> 18:05.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:05.167 --> 18:07.836
<i>- Into your hands, oh, God,</i>

18:07.920 --> 18:11.882
<i>we commend Your servant</i>
<i>Dick Marshall.</i>

18:11.965 --> 18:13.717
<i>- It doesn't matter.</i>

18:13.801 --> 18:17.096
God created no junk.

18:17.179 --> 18:20.098
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:20.182 --> 18:23.060
<i>- All that he did,</i>
<i>Dick offered love</i>

18:23.143 --> 18:25.229
<i>and compassion and faith</i>

18:25.312 --> 18:29.691
<i>shared through joy</i>
<i>and a bit of hope and magic.</i>

18:29.775 --> 18:32.528
<i>On behalf</i>
<i>of Dick Marshall's family,</i>

18:32.611 --> 18:34.738
<i>you are welcomed here.</i>

18:34.822 --> 18:38.659
<i>All are welcomed here...</i>

18:38.742 --> 18:41.161
<i>because as Dick</i>
<i>so amply enjoyed saying...</i>

18:41.245 --> 18:42.871
- Perfect. Thanks.

18:42.955 --> 18:46.041
<i>- That "God don't</i>
<i>make no junk."</i>

18:46.125 --> 18:48.710
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:48.794 --> 18:50.838
- Look at this one
with the wig flying back.

18:50.921 --> 18:53.549
- Dick looks like
he's terrified, you know.

18:53.632 --> 18:55.551
- In that one.
both: Yep.

18:55.634 --> 18:57.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:57.511 --> 19:00.639
- It was just so sudden.
It was heartbreaking.

19:00.722 --> 19:04.309
- Yeah. He was very supportive
of the move now

19:04.393 --> 19:09.314
to try to expand the diversity
of the Santa community

19:09.398 --> 19:12.609
<i>and trying to brainstorm,</i>

19:12.693 --> 19:15.195
like, how do we reach out,
how do we find those people?

19:15.279 --> 19:17.656
- Well, you can't put an ad
in the paper, say,

19:17.739 --> 19:21.577
"Any dwarfs out there
that want to be Santa Claus,

19:21.660 --> 19:23.745
"particularly if you're Jewish

19:23.829 --> 19:26.999
and of a different color."

19:27.082 --> 19:29.835
There's no way for us
to ask for that

19:29.918 --> 19:33.130
that I'm aware of
without offending.

19:33.213 --> 19:36.258
- There is that...

19:36.341 --> 19:39.970
conservatism sometimes in the
Santa community

19:40.053 --> 19:42.264
that's very closed.

19:42.347 --> 19:45.934
But I think that was
the nice thing with Dick,

19:46.018 --> 19:51.023
is that it didn't matter
what you look like.

19:52.316 --> 19:54.860
<i>Being Santa is in the heart.</i>

19:54.943 --> 20:02.034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:14.296 --> 20:15.881
- All right.
Whoa!

20:15.964 --> 20:18.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:18.383 --> 20:19.676
Stay.

20:19.760 --> 20:24.014
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:24.097 --> 20:28.143
How's this one?
Oh, this one's good.

20:28.226 --> 20:31.605
- There he is.
<i>- Ho, ho, ho!</i>

20:31.688 --> 20:34.399
- Hi.
<i>- It's nice to meet you.</i>

20:34.483 --> 20:35.901
- Now, I have a question.

20:35.984 --> 20:39.738
Is there anything
that we need to do or...

20:39.821 --> 20:43.408
I mean, have you ever had
a nonspeaking person there

20:43.492 --> 20:45.494
at Santa Camp
before or anything?

20:45.577 --> 20:48.914
<i>- This will be the first.</i>
- Oh, okay.

20:48.997 --> 20:50.707
[chuckles]
'Cause it's a little bit--

20:50.791 --> 20:54.962
You know, going into a new
situation with lots of people

20:55.045 --> 20:56.588
can be a little daunting.

20:56.672 --> 21:00.968
Because Fin Barre's
a Santa with spina bifida,

21:01.051 --> 21:04.513
and I don't know
if that's a situation--

21:04.596 --> 21:06.640
- Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho.

21:06.723 --> 21:09.142
- Doesn't have any problem with
the "ho, ho, ho" part, however.

21:09.226 --> 21:12.020
<i>- Yeah. That's right.</i>
[laughter]

21:13.397 --> 21:16.066
<i>- In here is...</i>

21:16.149 --> 21:18.276
the lair of Santa Fin.

21:18.360 --> 21:19.611
And there he is.

21:19.695 --> 21:21.363
- [grunts]
- [chuckles]

21:21.446 --> 21:24.199
<i>- [computerized voice]</i>
<i>I love everything about Santa.</i>

21:24.282 --> 21:26.702
- Really? I couldn't tell.

21:26.785 --> 21:30.664
- What's that device
that you're holding?

21:30.747 --> 21:32.457
<i>- My iPad.</i>

21:32.541 --> 21:35.252
- So Fin is what's called
a multimodal communicator,

21:35.335 --> 21:39.214
meaning he uses his hands,
his body, his iPad,

21:39.298 --> 21:42.718
<i>and his voice to communicate.</i>

21:42.801 --> 21:45.512
- Can it ever be hard
to communicate?

21:47.347 --> 21:48.598
<i>- Yes.</i>

21:48.682 --> 21:53.061
- Except when he has
the big red suit on.

21:53.145 --> 21:56.148
The magic just...
[snaps fingers] Clicks.

21:57.899 --> 22:00.944
- What's the best thing
about being Santa?

22:01.028 --> 22:06.700
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:06.783 --> 22:08.785
<i>- I fly around in a sleigh.</i>

22:08.869 --> 22:12.080
- Ho, ho, ho, ho.
- Your sleigh.

22:12.164 --> 22:16.418
Anytime anyone sees anything
that says "ho, ho, ho" on it,

22:16.501 --> 22:18.920
it ends up
in this room somehow.

22:19.004 --> 22:22.591
<i>That's a gift. That's a gift.</i>
<i>That's a gift. That's a gift.</i>

22:22.674 --> 22:25.093
<i>And he's got that whole</i>
<i>snow-globe thing</i>

22:25.177 --> 22:27.429
<i>going on here, too.</i>

22:28.805 --> 22:32.309
- So we need to do all sorts
of updates

22:32.392 --> 22:33.810
on the Santa Fin website.

22:33.894 --> 22:36.730
- Okay. And maybe
we might have some giveaway.

22:36.813 --> 22:38.774
I'm not quite sure
what that would be.

22:38.857 --> 22:40.984
- T-shirts.
- T-shirts.

22:41.068 --> 22:42.778
- Candy.
- [chuckles]

22:42.861 --> 22:45.947
<i>- I want my elves</i>
<i>to give out stuffed bears.</i>

22:46.031 --> 22:48.950
- You want to do that?
- Cool.

22:49.034 --> 22:53.163
- So, on the homepage, it says,
"It all started with a dream,

22:53.246 --> 22:56.416
"a dream to follow his passion
and be a real Santa,

22:56.500 --> 23:00.212
regardless of any obstacle
that may have been in his way."

23:00.295 --> 23:02.005
[both chuckle]

23:02.089 --> 23:04.674
- What are some
of those obstacles?

23:04.758 --> 23:07.469
- Well, what's happened a lot
in the past

23:07.552 --> 23:09.471
when we've reached out
to places,

23:09.554 --> 23:11.973
they're like,
"Yeah, a special--What?

23:12.057 --> 23:13.391
"No. What?

23:13.475 --> 23:16.770
No, we couldn't have
a special-needs Santa."

23:16.853 --> 23:20.774
And, I mean, I've had people
that have said to me, you know,

23:20.857 --> 23:22.651
"Can I catch what he has?"
It's like--

23:22.734 --> 23:24.236
- What?
- "I don't know,

23:24.319 --> 23:26.655
but you caught an awful lot
of stupid, like"...

23:26.738 --> 23:27.948
- Yeah, you caught stupid.

23:28.031 --> 23:30.659
- Fin, how did that
make you feel?

23:30.742 --> 23:32.744
<i>- Sad.</i>
- Sad? Yeah.

23:32.828 --> 23:36.039
<i>- Sad.</i>
- Yeah, it's super painful.

23:37.290 --> 23:39.376
[voice breaking]
I don't know, man.

23:39.459 --> 23:41.169
[sniffles]

23:41.253 --> 23:43.839
- He's typing something.

23:43.922 --> 23:45.423
- Go ahead, honey.

23:47.008 --> 23:51.012
<i>- I want to be a Santa</i>
<i>in a December parade.</i>

23:51.096 --> 23:52.264
- Okay.

23:52.347 --> 23:54.141
- What is it about being
in a parade

23:54.224 --> 23:56.518
that's, like,
so important to you?

23:56.601 --> 24:01.314
<i>- I want to show everyone</i>
<i>that I am the real Santa.</i>

24:02.357 --> 24:06.027
- It's his dream, so...
<i>- Yes.</i>

24:11.158 --> 24:13.618
- All right, so...

24:13.702 --> 24:15.495
Hi there, Kay.
This is Suki.

24:15.579 --> 24:20.542
I had texted you about a month
or so ago about the parade.

24:20.625 --> 24:22.294
<i>- Hello.</i>
- I'm calling.

24:22.377 --> 24:26.381
I know it's August, but
I've got a kind of wild idea.

24:26.464 --> 24:30.719
<i>- Well, maybe.</i>
<i>I don't know who--</i>

24:30.802 --> 24:33.930
<i>[line beeps]</i>
- Oh, no, I lost him.

24:34.014 --> 24:35.015
Unreal.

24:35.098 --> 24:37.851
[exhales deeply]

24:41.605 --> 24:43.231
[keys clacking]

24:43.315 --> 24:45.483
<i>- So we have been</i>
<i>reaching out to Santas</i>

24:45.567 --> 24:47.319
<i>of different backgrounds...</i>

24:48.820 --> 24:51.364
<i>Like this Santa named Levi.</i>

24:51.448 --> 24:52.866
<i>He's trans.</i>

24:52.949 --> 24:54.409
- Ho, ho, ho.

24:54.492 --> 24:57.579
Santa Levi,
aka Trans Santa here.

24:57.662 --> 25:00.749
<i>- Actually, he looks</i>
<i>pretty good as a Santa.</i>

25:00.832 --> 25:02.250
- [mouthing words]

25:02.334 --> 25:05.587
<i>- ♪ I don't want</i>
<i>a lot for Christmas ♪</i>

25:05.670 --> 25:08.340
<i>- That's what</i>
<i>we're looking for.</i>

25:08.423 --> 25:12.510
<i>[laughter]</i>

25:16.973 --> 25:21.811
- We literally went to Target
and bought a Santa onesie.

25:21.895 --> 25:23.313
[laughs]

25:23.396 --> 25:25.982
Look how cute we are.

25:26.066 --> 25:27.901
Look at Levi with the babies.

25:27.984 --> 25:30.445
- Most of the kids cried.
- [giggles]

25:30.528 --> 25:32.906
- I think the night before
and that morning,

25:32.989 --> 25:35.659
I, like, practiced
ho-ho-ho-ing

25:35.742 --> 25:37.702
'cause that was, like, really--

25:37.786 --> 25:40.288
I was like, oh, wait.
I have to like,

25:40.372 --> 25:42.499
talk to people in a Santa-y,

25:42.582 --> 25:46.461
like, boisterous like,
"ho, ho, ho," right?

25:46.544 --> 25:48.004
'Cause, you know, it takes
a while for your voice

25:48.088 --> 25:49.965
to change when you're taking
testosterone.

25:50.048 --> 25:52.592
But in a Santa suit,
everybody likes you,

25:52.676 --> 25:54.511
so it's fine.

25:54.594 --> 25:58.348
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:58.431 --> 26:00.016
- We met online.
- Yeah.

26:00.100 --> 26:02.644
- [clears throat] I was fresh
out of a relationship.

26:02.727 --> 26:04.854
<i>He was newish to Chicago.</i>

26:04.938 --> 26:06.731
<i>Can I talk about you</i>
<i>for a second?</i>

26:06.815 --> 26:08.149
- Yeah.
- When we met,

26:08.233 --> 26:10.902
Levi knew that he was a boy

26:10.986 --> 26:13.613
but had no desire
to ever transition.

26:13.697 --> 26:16.491
- I just didn't want to be
an old white guy

26:16.574 --> 26:21.246
<i>having privilege and not</i>
<i>recognizing privilege and--</i>

26:21.329 --> 26:23.832
I don't want to be that.

26:23.915 --> 26:25.208
I like being other.

26:25.292 --> 26:27.502
- And part of that is being
Trans Santa

26:27.585 --> 26:31.339
and being, like,
a super queer fat Mrs. Claus...

26:31.423 --> 26:33.967
[laughs]
And killing it.

26:34.050 --> 26:35.218
Check that out.

26:35.302 --> 26:36.678
- Oh, boo.
- Oh!

26:36.761 --> 26:38.680
Still have zero, by the way.
- Oh, I'm losing.

26:38.763 --> 26:41.349
When Heidi found out
there was a Santa Camp,

26:41.433 --> 26:44.060
she immediately was like,
"Yeah, we're going."

26:44.144 --> 26:45.437
And I was like, "Why?"

26:45.520 --> 26:47.605
- What is not appealing
about Santa Camp?

26:47.689 --> 26:50.150
I mean, come on!
That sounds amazing.

26:50.233 --> 26:51.860
'Cause to me, I think like,

26:51.943 --> 26:56.239
Santa in, like, big armchairs
that are cozy, right?

26:56.323 --> 26:59.534
So that's what I visualized.

26:59.617 --> 27:01.244
<i>Look at all that</i>
<i>wood paneling.</i>

27:01.328 --> 27:04.205
- Yeah. And a lot of red.

27:04.289 --> 27:06.374
- Oh.
- Oh.

27:06.458 --> 27:08.418
- They're all white.

27:08.501 --> 27:10.295
- Are they all white?

27:10.378 --> 27:11.921
- I mean...

27:12.005 --> 27:15.342
at a first visual capture,
they appear to be all white.

27:15.425 --> 27:16.468
- It's true.

27:16.551 --> 27:18.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:18.386 --> 27:20.930
Are you still
as excited to go as you were?

27:21.014 --> 27:24.559
- [exhales deeply]
- You okay?

27:24.642 --> 27:26.394
Like, I genuinely want to go

27:26.478 --> 27:29.856
and learn
how to be a better Santa.

27:29.939 --> 27:33.818
Hope I'm accepted
by the other Santas.

27:33.902 --> 27:35.612
- Fuck 'em if you're not, babe.

27:35.695 --> 27:38.073
- It's true, but--
- Like, come on.

27:38.156 --> 27:40.283
<i>[soft music]</i>

27:40.367 --> 27:43.244
<i>People need to see themselves</i>
<i>in role models.</i>

27:43.328 --> 27:45.580
<i>- For sure.</i>

27:45.663 --> 27:48.375
Like, if I saw
a trans Santa when I was a kid

27:48.458 --> 27:49.918
and I was like...

27:50.001 --> 27:53.463
you know, when I was a kid,
I didn't really know,

27:53.546 --> 27:55.340
like, what trans was.

27:55.423 --> 27:57.467
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:57.550 --> 28:01.388
It would be...comforting.
I don't know.

28:01.471 --> 28:04.808
- Empowering.
- Definitely empowering.

28:04.891 --> 28:07.185
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:07.268 --> 28:09.521
Yeah.

28:09.604 --> 28:12.273
Now I'm starting to get, like,
choked up a little bit.

28:12.357 --> 28:14.359
- I can tell.
- I don't know.

28:14.442 --> 28:17.987
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:18.071 --> 28:20.532
- What are you thinking?
- [chuckles]

28:20.615 --> 28:26.704
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:26.788 --> 28:30.375
- Sorry.
[sniffles]

28:30.458 --> 28:32.627
- It would have made
a difference for you.

28:32.710 --> 28:35.505
- Yeah.
[scoffs]

28:35.588 --> 28:37.549
Yeah.
[sniffles]

28:37.632 --> 28:44.722
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:48.226 --> 28:50.186
<i>[bright music]</i>

28:50.270 --> 28:52.730
- The preparations have begun.

28:52.814 --> 28:54.023
Here we go.

28:54.107 --> 28:56.860
Starting with the fat suit.

28:56.943 --> 28:59.821
- So how are you feeling?

28:59.904 --> 29:02.907
<i>- I am excited for Santa Camp.</i>

29:02.991 --> 29:05.994
- Oops. Now it's just
totally coming off.

29:06.077 --> 29:08.746
This needs to get fixed
as well.

29:08.830 --> 29:11.791
- You gonna wear this
at Santa Camp?

29:11.875 --> 29:13.668
Cool. It's gonna be perfect.

29:13.751 --> 29:15.378
- Fin is asking every day,

29:15.462 --> 29:17.547
"Is it time to go to camp?
Is it time to go to camp?"

29:17.630 --> 29:20.592
- I think it's gonna be hot
at camp, so...

29:20.675 --> 29:22.844
no velvet.

29:22.927 --> 29:25.054
- I get anxious.
I worry, for sure.

29:25.138 --> 29:26.514
I don't want him to get hurt.

29:26.598 --> 29:28.433
I particularly don't want
anybody to call him,

29:28.516 --> 29:29.851
like, the R word.

29:29.934 --> 29:32.020
There could be some people
that would think,

29:32.103 --> 29:34.022
"Oh, you know,

29:34.105 --> 29:38.401
shouldn't have someone like
that being Santa," you know.

29:38.485 --> 29:40.111
I mean, there could be somebody
in a group of 100 people

29:40.195 --> 29:41.738
that would feel that way.

29:41.821 --> 29:44.991
I mean, the probability
is fairly high, I would say...

29:45.074 --> 29:46.743
particularly old white men.
[chuckles]

29:46.826 --> 29:48.870
- You gonna bring
your beard, too?

29:48.953 --> 29:50.663
Yeah.

29:51.789 --> 29:54.125
It needs a good brush.

29:54.209 --> 29:57.962
<i>- It's amazing, really,</i>
<i>the things that he can do</i>

29:58.046 --> 30:00.882
<i>that they told me</i>
<i>he would never do.</i>

30:01.966 --> 30:04.886
<i>The doctor said</i>
<i>he'd never walk and talk,</i>

30:04.969 --> 30:07.013
<i>that he'd be a quadriplegic.</i>

30:07.096 --> 30:09.057
- Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho.

30:09.140 --> 30:12.769
- When you have spina bifida,
usually it's like...

30:12.852 --> 30:15.730
a lot of moms are told,
"Your son's gonna--

30:15.813 --> 30:17.482
"or your daughter's gonna be
a vegetable.

30:17.565 --> 30:19.734
Find a good institution
and visit them on the weekend,"

30:19.817 --> 30:21.194
which is what they told me.

30:21.277 --> 30:23.446
And I went,
"This is not your decision.

30:23.530 --> 30:25.698
And I am done
listening to this."

30:25.782 --> 30:27.408
<i>And I never looked back,</i>

30:27.492 --> 30:31.412
<i>and I never, ever stopped.</i>

30:31.496 --> 30:34.332
- What about that cool
"ho, ho, ho" vest?

30:34.415 --> 30:36.251
Mom made this for you.

30:36.334 --> 30:38.545
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:38.628 --> 30:39.921
- It's a long journey.

30:40.004 --> 30:43.591
[voice breaking] I mean,
30 years is a long time.

30:43.675 --> 30:45.593
It's a big chunk of my life

30:45.677 --> 30:48.930
that I've devoted
to this young man.

30:49.013 --> 30:52.058
I'm 65. I'm tired.
[chuckles]

30:52.141 --> 30:55.061
- That will be good
for Santa Camp.

30:55.144 --> 30:57.272
<i>- We are going to camp</i>

30:57.355 --> 31:02.610
to have Fin have the best
experience that he can

31:02.694 --> 31:04.612
because this is his passion.

31:04.696 --> 31:08.408
And oddly enough,
it's become mine as well.

31:08.491 --> 31:12.495
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:16.165 --> 31:19.294
<i>[animals chattering]</i>

31:22.964 --> 31:24.507
[indistinct chatter]

31:24.591 --> 31:27.552
<i>[Enya's "Only Time"]</i>

31:27.635 --> 31:34.726
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:35.977 --> 31:40.815
<i>- ♪ Who can say</i>
<i>where the road goes?</i>

31:40.898 --> 31:43.860
<i>♪ Where the day flows? ♪</i>

31:43.943 --> 31:46.863
<i>♪ Only time ♪</i>

31:46.946 --> 31:49.866
<i>♪ And who can say ♪</i>

31:49.949 --> 31:52.118
<i>♪ If your love grows ♪</i>

31:52.201 --> 31:53.453
[camera shutter clicks]

31:53.536 --> 31:55.330
<i>♪ As your heart chose? ♪</i>

31:55.413 --> 31:57.874
<i>♪ Only time ♪</i>

31:57.957 --> 32:00.335
- All right, let's start.

32:00.418 --> 32:01.836
Let's get to work.

32:01.919 --> 32:06.382
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:06.466 --> 32:08.635
- All right.
I'm taking this one.

32:08.718 --> 32:11.179
- A couple mosquitoes flying
around here.

32:11.262 --> 32:14.140
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:14.223 --> 32:15.683
- Good to see you, Santa.

32:15.767 --> 32:19.520
- Oh, and it's good to see you,
Santa, as well.

32:19.604 --> 32:21.898
- Ho!
all: Ho!

32:21.981 --> 32:25.276
- Ho, ho, ho!
all: Ho, ho, ho!

32:25.360 --> 32:29.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:29.614 --> 32:31.240
- Santa Camp is not something

32:31.324 --> 32:34.494
that I had grown up
envisioning myself doing,

32:34.577 --> 32:38.039
so this is definitely
a new one on me.

32:38.122 --> 32:41.501
I mean, Black Santa
is not widely celebrated.

32:41.584 --> 32:44.170
There's not
very many of us, so...

32:44.253 --> 32:47.090
oh, it's definitely gonna be
a strange experience.

32:47.173 --> 32:48.800
- This must be Santa.
- It is Santa.

32:48.883 --> 32:51.052
- Has to be a Santa.
- We're glad you're here.

32:51.135 --> 32:52.804
- I'm happy to be here.
- Yeah.

32:52.887 --> 32:57.725
- You're close with your shoes.
Orange is close to red.

32:57.809 --> 33:00.770
- I actually do not own
a lot of red.

33:00.853 --> 33:03.147
Most of the things
that I own are green.

33:03.231 --> 33:07.193
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:07.276 --> 33:12.365
<i>- ♪ Who can say</i>
<i>if your love grows ♪</i>

33:12.448 --> 33:16.285
- All right, we're gonna come
right up to the sign.

33:16.369 --> 33:18.287
Half circle around.

33:18.371 --> 33:21.791
Elves to the front.

33:21.874 --> 33:24.877
Are you getting excited?

33:24.961 --> 33:26.212
- Santa's here.

33:26.295 --> 33:29.841
- You with the white beard.
[laughter]

33:29.924 --> 33:31.259
- Smile.

33:31.342 --> 33:38.433
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:40.810 --> 33:43.896
[all cheering]

33:47.024 --> 33:49.444
- I say "Santa,"
you say "Claus."

33:49.527 --> 33:50.653
Santa!
all: Claus!

33:50.737 --> 33:52.113
- Santa!
all: Claus!

33:52.196 --> 33:54.240
- I say "Missus,"
you say "Claus."

33:54.323 --> 33:55.533
Missus!
all: Claus!

33:55.616 --> 33:56.909
- Missus!
all: Claus!

33:56.993 --> 33:59.287
- I say "Rudolph,"
you say "reindeer."

33:59.370 --> 34:00.705
Rudolph!
all: Reindeer!

34:05.626 --> 34:08.796
- I many times have,
in the past few weeks,

34:08.880 --> 34:13.384
thought that this is
really nuts, really crazy.

34:13.468 --> 34:16.929
<i>[soft music]</i>

34:17.013 --> 34:18.723
[balloon pops]
- Oh!

34:18.806 --> 34:20.600
- Oops.

34:20.683 --> 34:24.145
<i>- Santa Camps</i>
<i>generally attract</i>

34:24.228 --> 34:27.648
<i>gentlemen of a certain age.</i>

34:27.732 --> 34:31.652
Older gentlemen who have
cultivated fat tummies...

34:31.736 --> 34:35.823
[chuckles] And very serious
about their beards.

34:35.907 --> 34:40.328
Usually God-fearing kind of,
like, Vietnam-vet guys

34:40.411 --> 34:44.749
and Christian guys and...

34:44.832 --> 34:46.167
guys, you know?

34:46.250 --> 34:47.919
- Heads up.

34:48.002 --> 34:51.380
<i>- We're going</i>
<i>into Santa world, and...</i>

34:51.464 --> 34:53.966
<i>I have no idea</i>
<i>how it's gonna go,</i>

34:54.050 --> 34:57.512
because we are
very different...

34:57.595 --> 35:00.056
[chuckles]
Really different.

35:01.182 --> 35:02.934
- Are you nervous, Fin?

35:05.061 --> 35:08.815
<i>- Got to do it for The Fin</i>
<i>because it's his dream.</i>

35:08.898 --> 35:13.945
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:14.028 --> 35:15.738
Oh, damn it.

35:17.198 --> 35:19.200
- [moans]
- I know you're excited.

35:19.283 --> 35:21.828
Please try to calm down, okay?

35:21.911 --> 35:26.123
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:26.207 --> 35:28.543
[door opens]
Hi.

35:28.626 --> 35:31.712
<i>- Hi, everybody.</i>
<i>I am Santa Fin.</i>

35:31.796 --> 35:32.964
- Fin, your name tag.

35:33.047 --> 35:34.340
- We'll worry
about Wi-Fi later.

35:34.423 --> 35:35.883
- Oh, yes. Yeah.

35:35.967 --> 35:37.635
- Wi-Fi, where's the Wi-Fi?
- Yeah, right, right.

35:37.718 --> 35:38.928
Okay, that's for Fin.

35:39.011 --> 35:41.514
- Okay, there you go,
Santa Fin.

35:41.597 --> 35:43.558
- Yeah.

35:43.641 --> 35:46.477
- This is my son Fin.
I'm his momager.

35:46.561 --> 35:47.854
- Hi, Fin.
Pleasure to meet you.

35:47.937 --> 35:49.897
I'm Dave.
I'm one of the instructors.

35:49.981 --> 35:52.775
<i>- I've been Santa</i>
<i>for six years.</i>

35:52.859 --> 35:54.277
- Awesome. Awesome.

35:54.360 --> 35:57.989
- There you go, like that.
Look right at me.

35:58.072 --> 35:59.824
Now...

35:59.907 --> 36:01.325
There you go.

36:01.409 --> 36:03.619
All right.
Are you ready to go, Fin?

36:03.703 --> 36:04.912
Your turn, dude.

36:04.996 --> 36:06.664
All right,
and look right at the child

36:06.747 --> 36:10.376
like the child is telling you
what's on their list.

36:10.459 --> 36:12.295
<i>- I felt very nervous.</i>

36:12.378 --> 36:14.505
<i>But he usually</i>
<i>wins everybody over</i>

36:14.589 --> 36:17.884
<i>regardless</i>
<i>of all of the obstacles.</i>

36:17.967 --> 36:20.052
- All right, you're all set.
- All right.

36:20.136 --> 36:21.262
- And who's next?

36:24.974 --> 36:27.351
- Let me push the button here,
see if it goes on.

36:27.435 --> 36:29.437
[device beeps]

36:29.520 --> 36:33.107
<i>[magical music]</i>

36:33.190 --> 36:40.031
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:40.114 --> 36:43.492
- Smile.
[indistinct chatter]

36:43.576 --> 36:46.329
- Snow, let it snow,
let it snow.

36:46.412 --> 36:48.080
- That's a good shot.

36:48.164 --> 36:50.249
- They won't believe that
in Rhode Island.

36:50.333 --> 36:52.168
- [laughs]

36:52.251 --> 36:55.004
- So what was Christmas like
down in Arkansas?

36:55.087 --> 36:56.714
- Well, I actually grew up
in Texas.

36:56.797 --> 36:58.841
- Oh, you did? Okay.
- Yeah.

36:58.925 --> 37:00.301
My mom's a lesbian.

37:00.384 --> 37:05.306
So Santa was
a Black lesbian woman for me.

37:05.389 --> 37:06.599
- Okay.

37:06.682 --> 37:08.142
- I think...

37:08.225 --> 37:10.978
sometimes you just worry
that you're going to say

37:11.062 --> 37:13.356
the wrong thing
and offend somebody.

37:13.439 --> 37:14.941
<i>You know, you're just not sure</i>

37:15.024 --> 37:18.110
<i>how to deal with</i>
<i>those situations,</i>

37:18.194 --> 37:22.073
especially today, in today's
politically correct world

37:22.156 --> 37:24.075
and cancel culture
and everything.

37:24.158 --> 37:27.286
You're just so afraid
what to say.

37:27.370 --> 37:29.580
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you. I'm Suki.

37:29.664 --> 37:32.667
- Hi. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

37:32.750 --> 37:36.379
- We've tried to really work
on just making ourselves

37:36.462 --> 37:38.506
more familiar
with what's going on.

37:38.589 --> 37:41.509
And, I mean, you know,
we were talking today

37:41.592 --> 37:42.885
on another topic,

37:42.969 --> 37:45.680
but just
the whole pronouns issue,

37:45.763 --> 37:47.723
that for us old guys,

37:47.807 --> 37:52.061
it's like, "My pronoun?"
You know?

37:52.144 --> 37:54.689
Things have
really changed recently

37:54.772 --> 37:58.317
in acknowledging
the gender issues.

37:58.401 --> 38:00.569
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:00.653 --> 38:03.489
<i>- "Gender issues"?</i>
<i>And I was like...</i>

38:04.907 --> 38:07.284
<i>- Yep.</i>
<i>- They're trying.</i>

38:07.368 --> 38:09.453
<i>But there's some</i>
<i>other verbiage we could use</i>

38:09.537 --> 38:11.122
<i>other than, like, "issues."</i>

38:11.205 --> 38:14.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:20.923 --> 38:22.717
- Grab a seat.

38:24.635 --> 38:25.678
All right.

38:25.761 --> 38:28.764
So we have a lot of new Santas.

38:28.848 --> 38:30.766
<i>[soft music]</i>

38:30.850 --> 38:32.560
Chris, who is a Black Santa,

38:32.643 --> 38:35.396
he's from Little Rock,
Arkansas,

38:35.479 --> 38:38.315
and then Levi

38:38.399 --> 38:40.443
is transgender, male.

38:40.526 --> 38:43.154
So they're getting into this

38:43.237 --> 38:46.615
in a very different way
than most of us did.

38:46.699 --> 38:50.745
You know, there are things
we might have to think about.

38:50.828 --> 38:52.204
- We've got to get used to it,

38:52.288 --> 38:55.249
because as
the last census bureau said,

38:55.332 --> 38:57.209
we are a minority now.

38:57.293 --> 38:59.879
- So the biggest hurdle

38:59.962 --> 39:02.757
that's embedded
in everybody's mind

39:02.840 --> 39:06.802
is that Santa is a elderly,

39:06.886 --> 39:08.637
older white male,

39:08.721 --> 39:10.181
and it's the toughest thing.

39:10.264 --> 39:12.349
When somebody sees
a Black Santa, they're like,

39:12.433 --> 39:16.270
"Mm, oh, jeez, that's not
what we were raised with."

39:16.353 --> 39:17.688
- To me,
it wouldn't be a shock,

39:17.772 --> 39:19.190
but it would be different

39:19.273 --> 39:23.736
because it'll be the first time
I've seen one.

39:23.819 --> 39:25.905
- Yeah, okay, let's move along,

39:25.988 --> 39:28.074
'cause we still got
a lot to do.

39:29.700 --> 39:33.496
[indistinct chatter]

39:33.579 --> 39:34.955
I hope it works.

39:35.039 --> 39:37.500
- Yeah.
[laughter]

39:41.295 --> 39:44.215
[bell ringing]

39:44.298 --> 39:49.053
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:49.136 --> 39:53.641
<i>- As a school for Santas</i>
<i>and Mrs. Clauses and helpers,</i>

39:53.724 --> 39:55.726
<i>we try to cover</i>

39:55.810 --> 39:57.645
<i>the whole gamut</i>
<i>of being Santa.</i>

39:57.728 --> 40:00.856
all: Dasher, Dancer,

40:00.940 --> 40:03.442
Prancer, Vixen...

40:03.526 --> 40:06.987
<i>- You have to know the basics</i>
<i>of the Santa legend.</i>

40:07.071 --> 40:08.739
all: Rudolph.

40:08.823 --> 40:11.158
Dasher, Dancer, Prancer, Vixen,
Comet, Cupid...

40:11.242 --> 40:12.993
<i>- But you develop</i>
<i>your own Santa.</i>

40:13.077 --> 40:17.331
all: Dasher, Dancer, Prancer,
Vixen, Comet, Cupid, Donner.

40:17.414 --> 40:20.376
<i>- We have people who have</i>

40:20.459 --> 40:23.129
<i>20, 30 years of experience.</i>

40:23.212 --> 40:26.632
- Always
the first question is...

40:26.715 --> 40:28.843
"You're not the real Santa.

40:28.926 --> 40:31.053
I know you're not
the real Santa."

40:31.137 --> 40:34.098
What's your answer to it?
What's your answer to it?

40:34.181 --> 40:35.933
Anybody?

40:36.016 --> 40:38.727
<i>- Yes. I am real.</i>
- Excellent.

40:38.811 --> 40:41.522
It's exactly what I say--
"Of course I am. I'm Santa.

40:41.605 --> 40:44.358
Ow, ooh. Ow, that hurt.
I'm real. Look, pinch me."

40:44.442 --> 40:47.862
[excited chatter]

40:47.945 --> 40:49.947
<i>- We've got a lot</i>
<i>of Mrs. Clauses now,</i>

40:50.030 --> 40:52.032
<i>and they're looking</i>
<i>to figure out</i>

40:52.116 --> 40:55.536
<i>how they can really become</i>
<i>part of the community.</i>

40:55.619 --> 40:58.289
- Round ones on the front part.

40:58.372 --> 40:59.915
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

40:59.999 --> 41:02.501
[chatter continues]

41:02.585 --> 41:04.587
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:04.670 --> 41:08.549
[object thuds,
cheers and applause]

41:08.632 --> 41:11.469
<i>- We really try to make it</i>
<i>an interactive program.</i>

41:11.552 --> 41:15.222
- Okay, so Santa loves
to laugh, right?

41:15.306 --> 41:18.934
So what do you do first is
you start with a little giggle.

41:19.018 --> 41:23.981
[laughing]

41:24.064 --> 41:26.567
No.
- Please join me.

41:26.650 --> 41:28.611
[laughter]

41:28.694 --> 41:32.114
<i>- Can you say "ho, ho, ho"?</i>
<i>Come on, Fin.</i>

41:32.198 --> 41:37.077
- Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho, ho.
[applause]

41:37.161 --> 41:38.913
- Good job, Fin.

41:38.996 --> 41:41.540
<i>- The most common thing</i>
<i>we hear after camp is,</i>

41:41.624 --> 41:44.877
<i>"I think my brain's</i>
<i>gonna explode."</i>

42:12.696 --> 42:15.449
<i>- Being the only person</i>
<i>of color here,</i>

42:15.532 --> 42:19.161
<i>it was definitely lonely</i>
<i>and awkward,</i>

42:19.245 --> 42:20.788
<i>to say the least.</i>

42:20.871 --> 42:24.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:24.166 --> 42:28.045
- Does Santa have
a diversity problem?

42:28.128 --> 42:29.505
- Boy, that is a good question.

42:29.588 --> 42:33.384
Why is he predominantly white?

42:34.718 --> 42:37.263
Um...

42:37.346 --> 42:39.515
Hmm.

42:39.598 --> 42:41.600
- I don't know
if it's a diversity problem

42:41.684 --> 42:45.145
or it's just people accept
that Santa is a certain way.

42:45.229 --> 42:48.023
- [sighs]
- It's probably historical.

42:48.107 --> 42:49.400
- Yeah.

42:49.483 --> 42:53.904
And, actually, the first Santa
was from Turkey.

42:53.988 --> 42:56.282
So he really wasn't white.

42:56.365 --> 42:58.576
He was...

42:58.659 --> 43:01.161
olive, would you say?

43:01.245 --> 43:03.163
- Santa's an icon.

43:03.247 --> 43:07.126
<i>Coke was a big promoter</i>
<i>of what Santa looked like,</i>

43:07.209 --> 43:09.128
<i>to the point</i>
<i>where you have customers</i>

43:09.211 --> 43:12.298
<i>who come along and say,</i>
<i>"I want Santa."</i>

43:12.381 --> 43:14.383
And they know exactly
what they want.

43:14.466 --> 43:16.719
They want the Coke Santa.

43:16.802 --> 43:18.679
- Over all the years
I've done this,

43:18.762 --> 43:21.140
I have never been asked
by a child,

43:21.223 --> 43:22.683
"How come you're white?

43:22.766 --> 43:24.727
How come Santa
isn't Black like me?"

43:24.810 --> 43:26.478
<i>So kids don't see color.</i>

43:26.562 --> 43:31.692
- Do you find that
the challenge of being a Santa,

43:31.775 --> 43:35.529
when most of us look like this,
is tough,

43:35.612 --> 43:38.615
or do you think it's gonna
become more and more accepted?

43:38.699 --> 43:42.202
- I don't think it'll be
as tough as most would think

43:42.286 --> 43:46.749
because there is a request,
a need out there.

43:46.832 --> 43:48.917
For us, the closest Santa

43:49.001 --> 43:51.420
would have been
New Orleans or Houston.

43:51.503 --> 43:52.963
- Yeah.
- Five to nine hours away.

43:53.047 --> 43:55.424
So I'm gonna be my own.
- [chuckles]

43:58.385 --> 44:02.598
- Are you looking to be
Santa elsewhere?

44:02.681 --> 44:04.141
- Yes.
- In other words--

44:04.224 --> 44:06.685
okay.
- Yes.

44:06.769 --> 44:09.730
It's--that's...

44:09.813 --> 44:10.898
yeah.

44:10.981 --> 44:13.275
So...yeah.

44:15.527 --> 44:17.571
<i>I don't necessarily think</i>
<i>that other Santas</i>

44:17.654 --> 44:19.865
<i>were asked</i>
<i>those kind of questions.</i>

44:21.617 --> 44:23.786
There are definitely
a few Santas

44:23.869 --> 44:25.788
that are uncomfortable
with a Santa of color

44:25.871 --> 44:28.165
or, in general,
with me being here.

44:29.708 --> 44:33.253
<i>But it's not</i>
<i>a new experience to me</i>

44:33.337 --> 44:35.881
<i>because I've gone through it</i>
<i>all my life.</i>

44:40.636 --> 44:43.764
- It's not a ball, teddy bear.

44:43.847 --> 44:46.100
[dog whimpering]

44:46.183 --> 44:48.352
Santa, of course,
is the limelight,

44:48.435 --> 44:51.939
but Mrs. Claus has been
coming up into that limelight

44:52.022 --> 44:53.190
quite a bit in the last,

44:53.273 --> 44:55.275
I don't know,
eight to ten years.

44:55.359 --> 44:58.028
- I needed an outlet
for the seriousness of nursing.

44:58.112 --> 45:00.614
And now we're here.
So you just never know.

45:00.697 --> 45:03.951
- I think that the Mrs. Santas
tend to be overlooked a lot.

45:04.034 --> 45:07.830
Sometimes you feel like,
"Ah, nobody cares."

45:07.913 --> 45:09.957
- Santa and Mrs. Claus
don't always get along.

45:10.040 --> 45:12.459
No, because they're
two different people,

45:12.543 --> 45:16.296
sometimes with two different
opinions about things.

45:16.380 --> 45:18.507
Most of the time
they better, though.

45:18.590 --> 45:21.844
[indistinct chatter]

45:25.013 --> 45:28.559
- Any of you
who are Mrs. Clauses...

45:28.642 --> 45:30.144
it is a chore

45:30.227 --> 45:32.980
trying to make sure
they're all dressed

45:33.063 --> 45:35.858
and they look good
and they're presentable

45:35.941 --> 45:40.487
and they have their white
gloves and they're all clean.

45:40.571 --> 45:41.739
- That's interesting.

45:41.822 --> 45:43.240
After all these years,

45:43.323 --> 45:45.826
I wondered how my stuff
all got put together.

45:45.909 --> 45:47.244
[laughter]

45:47.327 --> 45:48.996
- Just a comment on that.

45:49.079 --> 45:53.500
It's good for the kids to see
that they're married,

45:53.584 --> 45:57.671
that they're married
like their parents are married,

45:57.754 --> 46:00.674
that it's not that
much different,

46:00.757 --> 46:04.178
except that he's Santa Claus
and that's Mrs. Claus.

46:04.261 --> 46:05.846
- [exhales deeply]

46:05.929 --> 46:09.766
- Santa is often considered
the lead performer,

46:09.850 --> 46:11.977
and Mrs. Claus
is the support character.

46:12.060 --> 46:15.647
How do each of you balance
your performances

46:15.731 --> 46:18.025
to share that spotlight?

46:18.108 --> 46:22.237
- I have heard Santas
ask for the pricing schedule,

46:22.321 --> 46:26.074
and it'd be $100
for me and Mrs. Claus.

46:26.158 --> 46:28.035
And they said, "Well, you know,
that's a little steep.

46:28.118 --> 46:30.412
How about if Mrs. Claus
doesn't come?"

46:30.496 --> 46:32.456
And he says,
"Then it'll be $150."

46:32.539 --> 46:36.793
[laughter and applause]

46:36.877 --> 46:39.379
- That's a good point.

46:39.463 --> 46:44.009
We have another idea to that.

47:00.984 --> 47:04.196
[crowd booing,
chattering angrily]

47:08.158 --> 47:09.326
- Let him have it!

47:09.409 --> 47:11.995
- Anybody know
how to spell "doghouse"?

47:12.079 --> 47:14.915
- Excuse me,
I'm looking for the real Santa.

47:14.998 --> 47:16.208
[laughter]

47:16.291 --> 47:17.834
- It's like when you go
to a show

47:17.918 --> 47:20.587
to see the Rolling Stones
and they have a warm-up act.

47:20.671 --> 47:25.592
[crowd chattering angrily]
[laughs]

47:25.676 --> 47:29.221
- Boo!
[dog barking]

47:29.304 --> 47:30.931
- No, that's not the way
we do it.

47:31.014 --> 47:32.975
- It's--it's--
- My turn.

47:33.058 --> 47:35.435
I don't even know
where to start with all this.

47:35.519 --> 47:37.062
But I will say that I think

47:37.145 --> 47:40.566
that your pricing structure
needs to be rethought.

47:40.649 --> 47:43.777
[laughter and applause]

47:45.696 --> 47:48.907
- [clears throat]
That was rough.

47:48.991 --> 47:49.866
- [sighs]

47:49.950 --> 47:51.577
<i>Can I help you, Santa?</i>

47:51.660 --> 47:52.786
Can you dress yourself?

47:52.869 --> 47:54.621
- Stop it!
- Are you gonna be okay?

47:54.705 --> 47:58.208
Do you need the fluff your fur?
'Cause--what the fuck?

47:58.292 --> 48:00.544
- Yeah, it was--
- No.

48:00.627 --> 48:02.504
During the Mr. and Mrs. Claus
panel, we, like,

48:02.588 --> 48:04.798
had to, like, nonverbally
check in with each other.

48:04.881 --> 48:06.466
- There was a lot
of hand squeezing.

48:06.550 --> 48:07.884
Like, "Let's hold
this together.

48:07.968 --> 48:09.344
Like, are you gonna
say something?"

48:09.428 --> 48:11.054
- Breathing.
- Yeah.

48:11.138 --> 48:12.973
- And, like, the consistent
narrative through that panel

48:13.056 --> 48:16.393
was, like, "Mrs. Claus'"
whole purpose

48:16.476 --> 48:19.146
is, like, keeping
her Santa together.

48:19.229 --> 48:20.731
- Yeah.
- Gross.

48:20.814 --> 48:23.567
Like, we're not there anymore,
I hope.

48:23.650 --> 48:25.986
- I wish we would have said
something when the guy said

48:26.069 --> 48:27.237
that it should be

48:27.321 --> 48:29.656
this traditional
"husband and wife" thing.

48:29.740 --> 48:32.451
- It didn't feel like a space
where I could be like,

48:32.534 --> 48:34.995
"I'm sorry. What the fuck?"

48:35.078 --> 48:36.330
That was my--
coming out of it, I really wish

48:36.413 --> 48:38.832
that I would have said
something

48:38.915 --> 48:40.542
or stood up in that moment.

48:42.044 --> 48:43.587
I think we're learning
what we can.

48:43.670 --> 48:45.589
And in the moments
where we just, like,

48:45.672 --> 48:47.466
are not getting any value
out of this,

48:47.549 --> 48:49.760
we're gonna go
and make our own fun.

48:51.845 --> 48:54.181
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

48:54.264 --> 48:55.974
[laughter]

48:56.058 --> 48:57.601
- We're stealing this.

48:57.684 --> 49:00.103
- This is officially
our golf cart now.

49:00.187 --> 49:03.065
[tires squealing,
engine whirring]

49:03.148 --> 49:06.943
- Don't tip.
- [screams, laughing]

49:07.027 --> 49:09.655
Uh-oh. We're off-roading now.
- Floor it!

49:09.738 --> 49:11.531
- Don't "transplain"
driving to me.

49:11.615 --> 49:13.533
- I'm sorry.
- [laughs]

49:13.617 --> 49:15.327
<i>[horn honks]</i>

49:15.410 --> 49:17.245
- Birdie's in the tree.

49:18.497 --> 49:21.333
- [imitates horn honking]

49:21.416 --> 49:24.753
[horn honks]
- Merry Christmas!

49:24.836 --> 49:26.880
- Santa Land.
- Santa Land.

49:26.963 --> 49:29.925
[tires squealing]
Oh. [giggles]

49:30.008 --> 49:32.219
[engine whirring, horn honks]

49:32.302 --> 49:33.971
[laughter]

49:34.054 --> 49:35.931
- Oh, no, that's the hawk.

49:36.014 --> 49:37.891
- Is that the red tail?

49:37.974 --> 49:40.227
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

49:40.310 --> 49:42.396
- [coughs]

49:42.479 --> 49:46.650
[imitates bird calling]

49:46.733 --> 49:48.318
[bird calling]

49:48.402 --> 49:51.363
[continues imitating
bird calling]

49:51.446 --> 49:55.992
- I'm not what you would call
a conventional Mrs. Claus.

49:56.076 --> 49:59.746
I guess you could say
I'm not a dress wearer.

49:59.830 --> 50:02.582
In literature and pictures,

50:02.666 --> 50:06.753
I don't think I've ever once
seen Santa

50:06.837 --> 50:09.756
with a woman with pants on.

50:09.840 --> 50:12.426
- [clicking tongue]

50:12.509 --> 50:15.303
[bird chirping]

50:15.387 --> 50:17.806
[indistinct chatter]
- That looks awful.

50:17.889 --> 50:19.766
- And she's got
a really cool belt.

50:19.850 --> 50:22.269
I think that ties
it all together.

50:22.352 --> 50:25.105
- What do I wear?
What does Mrs. Claus wear?

50:25.188 --> 50:27.774
So I have, you know,
the little colonial bonnet.

50:27.858 --> 50:30.485
Put a little holly in my hair.

50:30.569 --> 50:32.696
- Oh, God.
- I know, right?

50:32.779 --> 50:34.281
- Oh, my God.

50:34.364 --> 50:36.616
- You can make any kind
of music you want.

50:36.700 --> 50:40.620
Walmart, online, $18.

50:41.663 --> 50:46.334
- My view is Mrs. Claus
is Santa's wife.

50:46.418 --> 50:49.045
When he's not there,
she's in charge.

50:49.129 --> 50:51.590
She takes care of him
like any good wife, you know?

50:51.673 --> 50:55.886
- I'm sorry. I'm Dr. Claus.
Like, I am not the wife.

50:57.596 --> 51:00.098
Like, I have my PhD. You're not
gonna call me Mrs. Claus.

51:00.182 --> 51:02.017
I'm Dr. Claus.

51:02.100 --> 51:04.311
My spouse is trans,
and I'm queer.

51:04.394 --> 51:06.229
Like, actually,
when we come together,

51:06.313 --> 51:09.149
I really want to not bring up
the fact that we're married

51:09.232 --> 51:11.485
and instead really emphasize,
like, Santa's got a job,

51:11.568 --> 51:13.612
and I've got a job,
and we work together

51:13.695 --> 51:15.864
and really make
that space for folks.

51:15.947 --> 51:19.534
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:19.618 --> 51:21.912
- Yay.
- Bravo.

51:21.995 --> 51:25.999
[applause]

51:26.082 --> 51:29.336
- I love--I don't know--doctor.
That's, like, the best.

51:29.419 --> 51:31.254
That's so great.

51:31.338 --> 51:34.174
Yeah, I like the idea
that it can be fluid.

51:34.257 --> 51:37.552
And I like the idea
of being a goddess as well.

51:37.636 --> 51:39.846
Hey, you know,
Mrs. Claus is real.

51:39.930 --> 51:41.556
She's here.
She's a part of it.

51:41.640 --> 51:43.058
And we get to define her,

51:43.141 --> 51:45.560
and that's a great freedom,
I think.

51:45.644 --> 51:48.814
- Let me ask--how about pay?
- Oh, absolutely.

51:48.897 --> 51:50.857
Mrs. Claus
should have equal billing,

51:50.941 --> 51:53.485
because then it's not even
about negotiating,

51:53.568 --> 51:56.112
it's just knowing to have--

51:56.196 --> 51:57.447
It's courtesy and respect

51:57.531 --> 52:00.200
in terms of,
now we can set the tone.

52:00.283 --> 52:02.661
- One thing that I would like
to see changed is,

52:02.744 --> 52:06.373
I want to see pant suits
thrown in there somewhere.

52:06.456 --> 52:08.083
[laughter]

52:08.166 --> 52:10.293
- I'm just learning so much
just by what everybody says.

52:10.377 --> 52:14.089
It's like a potpourri of ideas
and information.

52:14.172 --> 52:15.507
It's like, "Wow."

52:15.590 --> 52:17.843
I'm glad I didn't miss
today's get-together.

52:17.926 --> 52:20.637
[applause]

52:20.720 --> 52:24.015
<i>[magical music]</i>

52:24.099 --> 52:27.519
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:27.602 --> 52:31.064
<i>all:</i>
<i>Ho, ho, ho! Ho, ho, ho!</i>

52:31.147 --> 52:35.151
Ho, ho, ho!

52:35.235 --> 52:37.821
Nice job.
We're getting there.

52:37.904 --> 52:40.574
[applause]

52:40.657 --> 52:43.869
We have a little presentation
and some information

52:43.952 --> 52:47.080
we want to share
before we have lunch.

52:47.163 --> 52:49.791
If you're a student
of Dick Marshall's,

52:49.875 --> 52:52.294
would you stand up, please?

52:52.377 --> 52:55.380
[bagpipe music playing]

52:55.463 --> 52:57.507
Not yet.
Not yet, Norm.

52:57.591 --> 52:59.384
Not yet.

53:02.929 --> 53:06.182
[voice breaking] Today
we're gonna recognize Dick.

53:09.352 --> 53:11.938
<i>Can we have</i>
<i>a moment of silence</i>

53:12.022 --> 53:14.482
<i>for Dick Marshall, please?</i>

53:14.566 --> 53:17.611
["Amazing Grace" playing
on bagpipes]

53:17.694 --> 53:24.784
♪ ♪

53:37.756 --> 53:39.633
[applause]

53:39.716 --> 53:42.844
[indistinct chatter]

53:45.221 --> 53:47.265
- I just want you to think
about us

53:47.349 --> 53:49.976
when you're doing your stuff
for this season.

53:50.060 --> 53:53.229
And if there's something that
bubbles up and you're thinking,

53:53.313 --> 53:55.690
"Wow, this might be a really
cool thing for those guys."

53:55.774 --> 53:58.652
What do you want to do, Fin?
Why don't you tell us?

53:58.735 --> 54:03.114
<i>- I want to be a Santa</i>
<i>in December parade.</i>

54:03.198 --> 54:05.492
- That's not easy.

54:05.575 --> 54:08.411
I mean, what happens is,

54:08.495 --> 54:10.997
they get a Santa who's local,

54:11.081 --> 54:15.001
and so he's there until he
takes his last sleigh ride.

54:15.085 --> 54:16.336
- That's right.

54:16.419 --> 54:18.296
<i>No, it's very territorial.</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

54:18.380 --> 54:20.465
<i>- There's a little bit</i>
<i>of competitiveness</i>

54:20.548 --> 54:22.592
around stuff, I've noticed.

54:22.676 --> 54:24.010
- Well--[clears throat]

54:24.094 --> 54:26.179
- I, literally, as his mom,
was telling him,

54:26.262 --> 54:27.973
"No, this is not going
to happen.

54:28.056 --> 54:29.683
You need to let go
of this dream."

54:29.766 --> 54:32.227
And he's like, "No, I'm not
letting go of this dream."

54:32.310 --> 54:34.104
<i>- What about my sleigh?</i>

54:34.187 --> 54:36.022
- So you want to be
in your sleigh

54:36.106 --> 54:37.399
when you're in the parade.

54:37.482 --> 54:39.192
- Oh, there's an idea.
<i>- Yes.</i>

54:39.275 --> 54:42.237
- Yeah.
- That's a big yes. Okay.

54:42.320 --> 54:45.198
<i>- It's a Portland Cutter.</i>

54:45.281 --> 54:49.035
<i>It was built</i>
<i>in the early 1900s.</i>

54:49.119 --> 54:51.246
- You could say,
"Well, we have a sleigh.

54:51.329 --> 54:52.747
We have a flatbed."

54:52.831 --> 54:56.376
Kind of put together
almost, you know, packages

54:56.459 --> 54:58.545
that you can offer to people.
- Oh, my God, okay.

54:58.628 --> 54:59.963
- Ho, ho, ho.

55:00.046 --> 55:02.298
- Would you wave?
Let me see your queen's wave.

55:02.382 --> 55:04.384
- Big waves, both sides, Fin.

55:04.467 --> 55:06.011
You need to work out
every day during this.

55:06.094 --> 55:07.971
- All right, we're gonna
start working out

55:08.054 --> 55:09.556
your arms there, Santa.

55:09.639 --> 55:12.100
- Left side, right side.

55:12.183 --> 55:14.978
Left side, right side.

55:15.061 --> 55:17.897
<i>- Great gigs can be hard</i>
<i>to get.</i>

55:17.981 --> 55:22.110
And if it doesn't happen,
it's gonna suck.

55:22.193 --> 55:24.320
It's gonna really suck.

55:30.952 --> 55:34.706
all: ♪ Here comes Santa Claus,
here comes Santa Claus ♪

55:34.789 --> 55:37.125
♪ Right down Santa Claus Lane ♪

55:37.208 --> 55:41.046
♪ Vixen and Blitzen
and all his reindeers ♪

55:41.129 --> 55:44.924
♪ Pulling on the reins ♪
[laughter]

55:45.008 --> 55:48.136
- So, Bob, you've got to tell
your Christmas Eve story.

55:48.219 --> 55:49.679
[chuckles]

55:49.763 --> 55:52.640
- People are coming in
and telling me what they want.

55:52.724 --> 55:56.227
This one teenage girl comes up.
She sat on my lap.

55:56.311 --> 55:59.064
[imitates flatulence]
And I went, "Oh, my God."

55:59.147 --> 56:01.316
They must have had
a chili cook-off

56:01.399 --> 56:03.151
the night before or something.

56:03.234 --> 56:06.571
[laughter and applause]

56:08.740 --> 56:12.368
- So who else has some stories
to share?

56:23.338 --> 56:25.799
- So the story...

56:25.882 --> 56:29.177
actually starts
a long time ago.

56:29.260 --> 56:32.680
I wanted my daughter to grow up
with representation

56:32.764 --> 56:35.141
of our family.

56:35.225 --> 56:39.604
So what I decided to do
was to get

56:39.687 --> 56:42.982
a Black Santa inflatable.

56:43.066 --> 56:46.778
Last year
I get a letter in the mail.

56:46.861 --> 56:49.697
And the letter...

56:49.781 --> 56:52.075
is...

56:52.158 --> 56:53.660
right here.

56:53.743 --> 56:56.037
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

56:56.121 --> 56:59.958
"Please remove your Negro
Santa Claus yard decoration.

57:00.041 --> 57:02.001
"You should not try to deceive
children

57:02.085 --> 57:05.672
"into believing
that I am a Negro.

57:05.755 --> 57:07.715
"I am a Caucasian,

57:07.799 --> 57:09.759
white man to you,

57:09.843 --> 57:12.178
"and have been
for the past 600 years.

57:12.262 --> 57:15.140
"Your being jealous of my race

57:15.223 --> 57:19.644
"is no excuse
for your dishonesty.

57:19.727 --> 57:23.273
"Besides that, you're making
yourself a laughingstock

57:23.356 --> 57:25.150
"of the neighborhood.

57:25.233 --> 57:28.069
"Maybe you should move...

57:28.153 --> 57:32.532
"to a neighborhood with
the rest of your race's kind.

57:32.615 --> 57:35.702
Yours truly, Santa Claus."

57:35.785 --> 57:38.163
[indistinct chatter]

57:38.246 --> 57:39.873
And...

57:39.956 --> 57:41.416
it came with a picture--

57:41.499 --> 57:45.795
Santa Claus with a thumbs-down.

57:45.879 --> 57:47.505
- Oh, my God.

57:47.589 --> 57:49.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

57:49.716 --> 57:53.636
- I brought this
to do this here.

57:53.720 --> 57:58.266
- Yeah!
[applause]

57:58.349 --> 58:05.231
<i>♪ ♪</i>

58:05.315 --> 58:08.401
I'm gonna be the Santa

58:08.484 --> 58:10.403
for kids that look like me
in my area.

58:10.486 --> 58:13.573
And coming here
has given me the tools

58:13.656 --> 58:15.783
to be able to do that
to the best of my abilities.

58:15.867 --> 58:17.827
And I'm so happy
that I got to come

58:17.911 --> 58:19.913
and spend this weekend
in New England.

58:19.996 --> 58:23.124
- Welcome.
[applause]

58:25.460 --> 58:27.587
- Who wants to follow
that story?

58:27.670 --> 58:30.590
[laughter]

58:30.673 --> 58:33.927
- All right, everybody up.
Let's go.

58:36.012 --> 58:37.931
- I don't know the words.

58:38.014 --> 58:39.807
- Let's all teach him.

58:39.891 --> 58:41.976
- All right, ready?
- Ready?

58:42.060 --> 58:43.228
- Who do we start with?

58:43.311 --> 58:45.104
- Dasher.
- Okay.

